<TITLE> PCL T20 League on cards </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 30 (bdnews24.com)  The Chittagong District Sports Association is planning to hold the Port City League (Twenty20 Cricket) with eight teams. The organisers on Monday placed their proposal to the Bangladesh Cricket Board and are now waiting for final approval to hold the Twenty20 league. We placed our proposal to the board, which assured us that they would let us know by April 3, said co-coordinator of the PCL Sirajuddin Mohammad Alamgir, also a BCB director. The PCL authority, however, has to ensure the board whether the pitch, floodlight and relevant facilities at Chittagong MA Aziz Stadium were playable. Alamgir said that the champions might be awarded between Tk 20 to Tk 15 lakh though it had yet to be finalised as they had estimated a budget of Tk 80 to 90 lakh. "We heard their proposal and asked them to clear a few things up," BCB director and tournament committee chairman Gazi Ashraful Hossain said. "BCB always wants to spread cricket and we welcome their initative." The Chittagong DSA plans to hold the Twenty20 league from April 29 to May 9 with the participation of Chittagong Abahani, Chittagong Mohammedan, Chittagong Brothers Union, Chittagong Port as well as four corporate houses  Ispahani Tea, Elite Paint, Partex and Gazi Tank. The organisers are also keen on holding a 70 players' auction  20 BCB contracted cricketers, 30 from the ongoing Dhaka Premier Cricket League and rest from Chittagong. The players will be divided into four categories and the base price of auction will be Tk 30, 20, 15 and 10 thousand respectively. bdnew
